THE University of Limpopo has called for qualifying potential students to apply to study at the institution for the 2022 academic year. The university said students who wanted to study towards a BSc in Agriculture majoring in agricultural economics, animal production, plant production, soil science, or environmental and resource studies could submit statements to arfsa@ul.ac.za. Those who want to study towards a BSc majoring in water and sanitation, mathematical science, life sciences, geology or physical sciences, should submit statements to arfsa@ul.ac.za. Those who want to study towards a Bachelor of Accountancy or Bachelor of Commerce can submit statements to Kamogelo.Ramokgopa@ul.ac.za. Applications will remain open until 4 February 2022; applicants will require a minimum of level 4 in mathematics and all relevant subjects. Lectures for first-entering students will therefore only commence on Monday, 7 February. The university said applications and registrations were strictly online to manage the risk of Covid-19 and to comply with the safety protocols in terms of the National Disaster Management Act.